research_municipality_step.notes: The City of Elgin, TX operates under a Home Rule, Council-Manager form of government, which is categorized as a mayor_council type. The Mayor and City Council members are elected. Information on elected officials was primarily sourced from the Texas Municipal League directory and cross-referenced with other public records. There were discrepancies between various sources, with the TML directory providing the most current list of council members. The Mayor Pro-Tem role was mentioned in one source but not consistently across the most recent lists of elected officials, so it is not included as a separate elected position.
